  "text": "Fresh blood was drawn from the jugular veins of horses, eosinophils were isolated, and were purified over discontinuous Percoll gradients as previously described [CITATION_1] . Purified eosinophils were suspended in Medium 199 containing 4 mM glutamine, 4.2 mM NaHCO 3 and penicillin/streptomycin (pH 7.2-7.3), stored at room temperature and used within 2 days.",
